main event: A radar operator at Wakkanai, Japan detected an unidentified aircraft on 6 November 1948, estimated to have circled the radar site for one hour and five minutes.
interesting points: The radar blip occasionally appeared as two aircraft dogfighting,The object was evaluated as a Soviet aircraft conducting electronic reconnaissance,No visual observations were made due to poor weather conditions,The aircraft was detected moving at speeds varying from 160 to 240 miles per hour,The incident lasted for 65 minutes while the radar operator monitored the target.
